data.description: Nestled on 30 acres of picturesque landscape in the heart of Upshur County, Texas, this charming 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom 1,682 sq ft home is a captivating blend of rustic allure and modern comfort. Originally constructed in 1980, this residence has undergone a recent transformation, embracing a contemporary open-concept design. The house exudes warmth, thanks to the beautiful wood grain vinyl plank floors that stretch throughout. A 2-car garage provides shelter for vehicles, while a detached shop caters to a myriad of potential uses. Beyond this sanctuary lies a nature lover's paradise, where whitetail deer roam freely, offering both hunting and observation. Discover the serenity of country living as Glade Creek gracefully meanders along the northern border of the property. Whether you seek a peaceful retreat, haven for wildlife enthusiasts, or a canvas for outdoor exploration, this property beckons with its diverse offerings in a setting that encapsulates the essence of country living.
